# gen160 (E1): compositional emergence — the social half, ratcheted. Six
# subsystems cooperate over fresh vocab (thora/parrot/kiwi): social register,
# name memory, possession memory, KB fact intake, discourse reference (the
# pronoun "it" binds to the last subject), and the personal summary that reads
# back what earlier turns stored.
> hey
< Hi there!
> my name is thora
< Nice to meet you, thora!
> i have a parrot named kiwi
< Got it: your parrot is called kiwi.
> kiwi is a bird
< Learned: bird(kiwi).
> is it a bird?
< Yes.
> what is my parrot called?
< kiwi.
> what is my name?
< Your name is thora.
> what do you remember about me?
< I remember: your name is thora; your parrot is kiwi.